"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 162 "As you may have noted the addition
/subtraction operatios where carried out while the multiplication/divi
sion operations were just indicated.  The Maple commands  " }{TEXT 
264 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 265 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 
298 "  can be used to rearrange and manipulate algebraic sums and prod
ucts of polynomial expressions.  Go back to each of your calculations \+
of a., b., c. and d. and add to each line a command to expand the calc
ulation and a command to simplify the caclulation.  E.g.,  the line fo
r a. would change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 4 "f*g;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 
"to " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "f*g; expand(f*g); si
mplify(f*g);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,(*$)%\"xG\"\"$\"\"
\"F)*$)F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&F,F)F'F)F-F),**&\"\"'F)F&F)F)*&\"#6F)F+F)F)*&F1
