-1 17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 268 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }
{TEXT 269 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 43 "  have on the way the calculation
 appears. " }{TEXT 306 223 "In the first line it simply puts the probl
ems ( but it will do the add and subtract parts of the problems).  The
 second line does the multiplication and division part of the problems
.  The third line simplfies the problems." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Maple commands " }{TEXT 266 
16 "expand, simplify" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 267 6 "normal" }
{TEXT -1 483 " can be use to rearrange, manipulate and simplify (cance
l common factors) algebraic sums, products and quotients of rational e
xpressions.   When a rational expression is normalized, any common fac
tors are cancelled.  Go back to each of your calculations of e., f., g
., h. and i. and add to each line a command to expand the calculation,
 to normalize the calculation, to simplify the calculation and both ex
pand and normalize the calculation.  E.g., the line for e. would chang
e from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "F*H/G;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "to" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 99 "F*H/G; expand(F*H/G); normal(F*H/G)
; simplify(F*H/G); expand(normal(F*H/G)); normal(expand(F*H/G));" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
