{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"HG,(*$)%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"F**$)F(\"\"#F*!\"\"*&F-F*F(F
*F." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 650 "In those cases where Maple did n
ot find enough linear factors, there is a reason why Maple did not.  M
aple makes an assumption that if the coefficients of a polynomial are \+
all given exactly (as integers or rational numbers [ratios of integer]
), then you are only interested in finding exact factors (factors wher
e the coefficients are integers or rational numbers).  The Fundamental
 Theorem of Algebra doesn't guarantee that the factors of  a polynomia
l will necessarily have the same kind of coefficients as the polynomia
l, only the polynomial can be factored.  You can force Maple to report
 additional (approximate) factors.  For example,  compare:" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "fact
or(h);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&*$)F%
\"\"#F&F&\"\"&!\"\"F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "fa
ctor(h,sqrt(5));" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&%\"xG\"\"\"*$
\"\"&#F&\"\"#F&F&,&F%F&F'!\"\"F&,&F%F&F&F&F&" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 52 "What is the difference?  \+
The extra-term is called a " }{TEXT 280 18 "field extension.  " }
{TEXT -1 178 "Adding it tells Maple to consider additonal factors wher
e the coefficients are allowed to include elements from the field exte
nsion.  It is fairly clear from the factoriztion of " }{TEXT 281 1 "h
" }{TEXT -1 280 " all by itself that something involving  sqrt(5)  wou
ld have to be included.  However, there are problems where there is no
t a obvious clue as to which specific field extension should be added.
  If you are willing to accept an appropriate solution, then using the
 field extension " }{TEXT 282 4 "real" }{TEXT -1 179 " tells Maple to \+
factor the polynomial using a floating point approximation scheme.  Fo
r example, consider (here I am pretending I don't see that adding  sqr
t(5) would be optimal):" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(h);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&*$)F%\"\"#F&F&\"\"&!\"\"F&" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "factor(h,real);" }}{PARA 11 
"" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+xz1OA!\"*F&F&,&F%F&$F&\"\"!F
&F&,&F%F&$\"+xz1OAF)!\"\"F&" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 91 "Finally, the Fundamental Theorem of Algebra doe
